premise_source_doc_sentence: It was first published in paperback by Ballantine Books in June , 1973 as the fifty-eighth volume of its Ballantine Adult Fantasy series ; it was the only nonfiction entry in the series .
Final Fantasy IV introduced innovations that became staples of the Final Fantasy series and role-playing games in general .

After the termination of the Adult Fantasy series , Ballantine continued to publish fantasy but concentrated primarily on new titles , with the older works it continued to issue being those with proven track records .
